Max REE, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 27, 1937. David Schwartz, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal., for the United States.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
